ğŸ§¬ Reflexive Schema

Add this file: schemas/reflexive.schema.json

{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "title": "Reflexive Operation Schema",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["timestamp_utc","operation","state","confidence"],
  "properties": {
    "timestamp_utc": {"type": "string","format": "date-time"},
    "operation": {"type": "string"},
    "state": {"type": "string"},
    "confidence": {"type": "number","minimum": 0,"maximum": 1},
    "comment": {"type": "string"}
  }
}

Every operation (verify, heal, federate, attest, etc.) produces a reflexive record:

{"timestamp_utc":"2025-11-04T00:00:00Z","operation":"verify","state":"consistent","confidence":0.9999}


